    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Those 'Safe' Cigarettes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Anjali D'Souza, says concept of 'safer' cigarette is ridiculous (Oct 4 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Claims About Safer Cigarette Are Disputed'' (news item, Oct. 4): What is the point of a ''safer'' cigarette? If it were less addictive, if it were to ease the process of quitting smoking, then surely a tobacco company like R. J. Reynolds would not sell it. Who are the consumers of this cigarette expected to be? Potential smokers who want to lead a ''healthy'' lifestyle? A ''safer'' cigarette -- what a ridiculous concept.</p>
        <p>ANJALI D'SOUZA  New York, Oct. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
